SIMPLE: ignoble
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ignoble
<hw>Ig*no"ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ignobilis</ets>; pref. <ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>nobilis</ets>
noble: cf. F. <ets>ignoble</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Noble</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of low birth or
family; not noble; not illustrious; plebeian; common; humble.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I was not <qex>ignoble</qex> of descent.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her royal stock graft with <qex>ignoble</qex> plants.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not honorable, elevated, or generous;
base.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'T is but a base, <qex>ignoble</qex> mind,⟦br⟧
That mounts no higher than a bird can soar.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Far from the madding crowd's <qex>ignoble</qex> strife.</q>
<rj><qau>Gray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Not a true or noble falcon; --
said of certain hawks, as the goshawk.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Degenerate; degraded; mean; base; dishonorable;
reproachful; disgraceful; shameful; scandalous; infamous.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ignoble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ignoble
<hw>Ig*no"ble</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To make ignoble.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ignobleness</ent>⟦br⟧
